[medium] src/composables/useDashboardSuggestions.ts:98 (concurrency/races)
refreshHistorySuggestions fans out accepted/rejected/superseded requests through the same useDataApi/useAxios execute instance. VueUse useAxios defaults abortPrevious to true and execute returns a shared thenable, so starting the second and third calls aborts/replaces the earlier calls; the history tab can end up missing accepted/rejected rows or duplicating whichever request finishes last.
Suggested fix: Do not use one useAxios execute concurrently here. Fetch the three statuses sequentially with await in a loop, or create independent request executors per status before combining the results.
Guidance: In src/composables/useDashboardSuggestions.ts, update refreshHistorySuggestions so the accepted/rejected/superseded history requests are not launched concurrently through the single fetchHistoryRequest executor returned by useDataApi. The minimal safe change is to replace Promise.all(statuses.map(...fetchHistoryRequest...)) with a sequential loop: initialize const collected: DashboardSuggestion[] = []; for each status of ['accepted','rejected','superseded'], await fetchHistoryRequest(buildDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint(sspId.value, status)), then push ...(response?.data.value?.data ?? []) into collected; after the loop set historySuggestions.value = collected. Keep the existing early return for missing sspId. Do not change the documented three separate status requests into a comma-separated status query. Avoid reading from the shared historySuggestionsLoading/data state to build results; use each awaited response so rows from earlier statuses are not overwritten by later execute calls.

